          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_InvoicePaymentRetrieve_EFT",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve invoice payment details from a view named "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Invoice.vwInvoicePayments",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". It allows filtering by either an invoice ID or an invoice number. The procedure logs its execution details, including any exceptions encountered, using another stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "dbo.USP_AppLogCreate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The procedure is intended for reporting purposes, specifically focusing on payments made via EFT (Electronic Funds Transfer), checks, or manually."
        }
      ]
